<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Uhl</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-24"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                    1896</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The superior court refuses to furnish a certified copy of the proceedings
                            in the trial of Sanguily. I am translating the correspondence for
                            transmission to you.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>